  "time_ut": 1662105470,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db1\u0db1\u0dca\u0daf\u0dbd\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0da7 \u0db8\u0db8 \u0dba\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0db8\u0dca - \u0dc3\u0db6\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Instead of Nandalal I will go - Sabri",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Former Finance Minister and current Foreign Minister Mr. Ali Sabri said in Parliament that it is false that the Governor of the Central Bank took the decision to not pay the debt and that decision was taken by talking to everyone.",
        "Mr. Ali Sabri also said that if anyone wants to remove the Governor of the Central Bank, he is ready to resign for him.",
        "\"Paying the debt is very important, but if your children are at home without food, if they are hospitalized without medicine, if they cannot get transportation tomorrow, then they have to make a decision that they will collect all their money and pay the debt? Will they feed the children?",
        "Don't impose that decision on anyone else. I took that decision after talking to everyone. If there is a mistake, don't run away. I was then the finance minister. I got that proposal from the central bank. I spoke with the central bank. The Minister of Finance spoke to the officials and spoke to the President twice. A special committee had been appointed and discussed with it, spoke with international experts and Mr. Harsha de Silva.",
        "The only thing we did was we decided not to pay the money we had. No money to pay. 203 million US dollars should have been paid. There is only 37000 in the treasury.",
        "There is 500 million US dollars to pay for the purchase of essential goods. Do they pay? Paying off debt? I discussed and took that decision. Mr. Nandalal Weerasinghe gave advice for that decision. If anyone wants to send it, I will.",
        "I fearlessly say that the people are benefiting today due to the decisions he made. Don't follow people for lies.\""
      ],
